<s> Strict documents are correctly guesses as strict and remain so, but Tidy and the W3C validator seem to have disagreements on a few things, like whether CITE and P belong inside BLOCKQUOTE which, as I recall, is the reason Tidy sees Transitional even when it really is a Strict-compliant document source.  </s>
<s> Also, Tidy does not yet know about XHTML Basic; it guesses that doctype as Strict and overwrites the DTD accordingly.  </s>
<s> No real harm done, except when I try to demonstrate that doctype and Tidy recursively turns everything into Strict, it voids the point of having that new subset in the first place.  </s>
<s> Looking back, the bug appears to systematically affect Framest and Basic doctypes, while overall validity interpretation bugs are most probably caused by disagreements about what is an inline and what is a block element.  </s>
<s> (on a side note, I never cease to be amazed at the discrepancies between what Tidy, W3C validator and WDG validator consider to be valid content for block elements) I hope the above will be of help.  </s>
